        <div class="postInner">
            <div class="paragraph">
                                
                <div style='min-height:40px'><IDXSKIP><div style="text-align: center"><br><br></div></IDXSKIP><div style="text-align: center"><span style="font-size:medium; color: #33cccc"><br><br></span></div><div><div style="color: #260a00; font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px; text-align: center; background-color: #ffffff"><span style="font-size:x-large; font-family: 'trebuchet ms', sans-serif; color: #351c75">Храм Санбо-дзи</span></div><div style="color: #260a00; text-align: center; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:13px; background-color: #ffffff"><span style="font-size:large; font-family: 'trebuchet ms', sans-serif">  </span><span style="font-size:medium; font-family: 'trebuchet ms', sans-serif"><span style="color: #741b47">*&#9679;*&#9679;*</span>  Северо-Восток области Takao в Ukyo-ku ( Запад )  <b>&#39640;&#38596;&#26041;&#38754;&#12539;&#21491;&#20140;&#21306;</b> <span style="color: #741b47"> *&#9679;*&#9679;*</span></span></div></div><div style="color: #260a00; text-align: center; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:13px; background-color: #ffffff"><br><br></div><div style="color: #260a00; text-align: center; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:13px; background-color: #ffffff"><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px; text-align: start"><div style="text-align: center; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:13px;"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/img_0.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; background: none" target=_blank><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452598884214/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/img_0.jpg?height=268&width=399" border="0" height="268px;" width="399px;" style="border: 0px; padding: 0px; width:385px; height:266px;"></a> </div></div><div style="font-size:13px;"><br><br></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span lang="ru"><span style="font-size:medium;"><span title="This Sanbouji Temple which belongs to Nichiren sect of Buddhism carries a title of Mt.">Это Храм Sanbouji Храм, который принадлежит секте Ничирен буддизма носит название горы </span><span title="Kinei.">Kinei. </span><span title="It was founded in 1628 to welcome a priest called Nichigo Jonin as a training ground of monks to practicing asceticism.">Он был основан в 1628 году, чтобы приветствовать священника Nichigo Jonin  и как как учебный полигон для монахов практикующих аскетизм. </span><span title="The temple is built on the foot of a mountain an it seems like a Temple and a Shrine combined into 1 place.  ">Храм построен у подножия горы и выглядит как храм и Святилище объединенное в одном месте.</span></span></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><br><br></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px; text-align: start"><div style="text-align: center; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:large;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-size:large; color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000"><span style="background-color: #20124d">  <b><span style="color: #ffd966">&#9679; </span></b>Nichiren &#26085;&#34030; </span><b><span style="color: #ffd966"><span style="background-color: #20124d">&#9679;</span> </span></b><span style="background-color: #20124d"> </span></span></span></div><div style="text-align: center; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:large;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-size:large; color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000"><span style="background-color: #20124d"><br><br></span></span></span></div><div style="text-align: center; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:large;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-size:large; color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000"><span style="background-color: #20124d"><div class="sites-embed-align-center-wrapping-off" style="clear: both; margin: 5px auto"><div class="sites-embed-border-off sites-embed" style="margin: 5px auto 0pt; border: 1px solid #a09681; color: #260a00; font-size:12px; width:480px; font-family: Koulen, cursive !important"><div class="sites-embed-content sites-embed-type-youtube" style="text-align: left; overflow: hidden; background-color: #ffffff"></div></div></div><br><br></span></span></span></div></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><br><br></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span lang="ru"><span style="font-size:medium;"><span title="&#9670; Nichiren &#26085;&#34030; was a Buddhist monk who lived during the Kamakura period (1185–1333) in Japan.">&#9670; Ничирен &#26085; &#34030; был буддийским монахом, который жил в период Камакура (1185-1333) в Японии. </span><span title="Nichiren taught devotion to the Lotus Sutra, which claims to contain Gautama Buddha's teachings towards the end of his life, as the exclusive means to attain enlightenment.">Ничирен учил преданности Сутре Лотоса, которая утверждает, что содержит учение Гаутамы Будды к концу своей жизни, как эксклюзивные средства для достижения просветления. </span><span title="Nichiren believed that this sutra contained the essence of all of Gautama Buddha's teachings related to the laws of causality, karma, and leading all people without distinction to enlightenment.    ">Ничирен верел, что в этой сутре содержится суть всех учения Гаутамы Будды, связанных с законами причинности, кармы, и ведет всех людей без различия к просветлению.</span></span></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span style="font-size:10pt; background-color: transparent"> </span><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452596071414/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/CIMG7480%20%28420x315%29.jpg?height=300px;&width=400px;" style="font-size:10pt; background-color: transparent"> </div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><br><br></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span lang="ru"><span title="A past time great tea master Yamada Sohen &#65288;1627&#65374;1708&#65289;was once resided in one of the houses in the precincts called Shiho-an during the practice of his way of tea."><span style="font-size:medium;">В давние времена великий мастер чая Ямада Sohen &#65288;1627&#65374;1708&#65289; проживал в одном из домов  называемых Шихо-ан во время практики его пути чая. </span></span><span title="A stone monument commemorating the remain of Shiho-an in the back side of the temple near a pond in the middle of woods.   "><span style="font-size:medium;">Каменный памятник Shino-an позади храма около пруда окруженный лесом.</span><br><br></span></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><br><br></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"> <img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452596226713/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/CIMG7532%20%28420x315%29.jpg?height=300px;&width=400px;" style="font-size:10pt; background-color: transparent"></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><br><br></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span style="font-size:medium;"> One of the Seven Fortunate Gods &quot; Daikokuten &quot; has been worshipped since its main hall was granted to this place. The building was used for the ritual of inauguration of late Emperor of Showa.</span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span style="font-size:medium;"><br><br></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span lang="ru"><span style="font-size:medium;"><span title="One of the Seven Fortunate Gods &quot; Daikokuten &quot; has been worshipped since its main hall was granted to this place.">Здесь поклоняются одному из семи богов Удачи Daikokuten. </span><span title="The building was used for the ritual of inauguration of late Emperor of Showa.      ">Здание использовалось для ритуалов инаугурации покойного императора периода Showa.  </span></span></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span lang="ru"><span title="The building was used for the ritual of inauguration of late Emperor of Showa.      "><span style="font-size:medium;"><br><br></span></span></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px; text-align: start"><div style="text-align: center"><span style="font-size:medium;"><span style="background-color: transparent">Эбису (</span><span style="background-color: transparent">   Ebisu) </span></span></div><div style="text-align: center"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/myoenji-miao-yuan-si-da-hei-tian/1273415997.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: medium; text-align: left; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size:0in; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial" target=_blank><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1447377569934/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/myoenji-miao-yuan-si-da-hei-tian/1273415997.jpg" border="0" height="230px;" width="229px;" style="border: 0px; padding: 0px; width:182px; height:184px;"></a><span style="text-align: left; font-size:medium; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif"> </sp