-size:xx-small;"> </span></a><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/CIMG7505%20%28420x315%29.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; background: none" target=_blank><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452596152640/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/CIMG7505%20%28420x315%29.jpg?height=240&width=320" border="0" height="240px;" width="320px;" style="border: 0px; padding: 0px; width:271px; height:213px;"></span></a></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;">  </div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px; text-align: start"><span style="background-color: transparent"><div style="text-align: center"><span style="font-size:medium;"><span style="background-color: transparent">Когда вы поднимитесь к вершине, первое, что вы заметите это ящик, наполненный куклами Дарума. Там находится окошко, куда вы платите 1000 йен за 1 Даруму. Обратите внимание, что есть крошечное отверстие в нижней части каждой Дарума, и там листок бумаги. Этот листочек с предсказание называется Omikuji. вы прочли ваше предсказание, вы можете его сохранить или завязать бумажку на ветку дерева для большего эффекта получения удачи.</span><span style="background-color: transparent"> Omikuji доступны в большинстве храмов, и остаются одним из традиционных видов деятельности, связанных с святынями.</span></span></div><div style="text-align: center"><span style="font-size:10pt; background-color: transparent"><br><br></span></div><div style="text-align: center"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/omikuji.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size:0in; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial" target=_blank><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452602515887/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/omikuji.jpg?height=320&width=307" border="0" height="320px;" width="307px;" style="border: 0px; padding: 0px; width:229px; height:243px;"></a><span style="font-size:medium; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif"> </span><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/Fotolia_27622146_S.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size:0in; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial" target=_blank><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452602512067/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/Fotolia_27622146_S.jpg?height=267&width=400" border="0" height="267px;" width="400px;" style="border: 0px; padding: 0px; width:365px; height:244px;"></a></div><IDXSKIP><div style="text-align: center"><br><br></div></IDXSKIP><div style="text-align: center">Виды фортуны Омикудзи.</div><IDXSKIP><div style="text-align: center"><br><br></div></IDXSKIP><IDXSKIP><div style="text-align: center"><br><br></div></IDXSKIP><div style="text-align: center"><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium; text-align: left"><div style="text-align: center"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452602519709/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/syomon04.jpg" border="0" style="background-color: transparent"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/daikichi.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; background: none" target=_blank><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452602507657/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/daikichi.jpg?height=315&width=400" border="0" height="315px;" width="400px;" style="border: 0px; padding: 0px; width:399px; height:317px;"></a></div><div style="text-align: center"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/syomon04.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; background: none" target=_blank></a><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/daikichi.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; background: none" target=_blank><br><br></a></div></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;">Общий уровень удачи &quot; unsei &#36939;&#21218; &quot;</span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;"><br><br></span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;">1. &#22823;&#21513; (daikichi) Великое благословение  </span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;">2. &#20013;&#21513; (ch&#363;kichi) Среднее благословение  </span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;">3. &#23567;&#21513; (sh&#333;kichi) Небольшое благословение</span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;">4. &#21513; (kichi) Благословение </span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;">5. &#26410;&#21513; (suekichi) Около Благословения</span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;">6. &#20982; (ky&#333<img class="smile" alt=";)" src="http://static.diary.ru/picture/1136.gif"> Проклятие </span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;"> 7. &#22823;&#20982; (daiky&#333<img class="smile" alt=";)" src="http://static.diary.ru/picture/1136.gif"> Великое проклятие</span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><br><br></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif"><div><span style="font-size:medium;"><span style="background-color: transparent">&#39000;&#26395; &#65288;negaigoto&#65289; </span>пожелания и желания</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#24453;&#20154; (machibito) кто-то вас ждут</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#22833;&#29289; (usemono) то, что вы потеряли</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#26053;&#34892; (tabidachi) путешествия</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#21830; &#22770; (akinai) бизнес</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#23398;&#21839; (gakumon) изучение и обучение</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#30456; &#22580; (Soba) фондовый рынок</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#20105; &#20107; (arasoi) спор</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#24651;&#24859; (Renai) роман</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#36578; &#23627; (yautsuri) движущиеся резиденции</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#20986;&#29987; (osan) беременность и рождение</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#30149; &#27671; (yamai) болезни</span></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;">&#32257; &#35527; (endan) предложение руки и сердца</span></div></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:medium;"><br><br></div></div></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px; text-align: start"><span style="font-size:10pt; background-color: transparent"><br><br></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span style="font-size:medium;"><span style="background-color: transparent">Храм имеет большое дерево Shidare Сакура (вишни под названием &quot;</span>Gosha Gaeshi-no Sakura<span style="background-color: transparent">&quot;<img class="smile" alt=";)" src="http://static.diary.ru/picture/1136.gif"> пересаженную сюда из императорского дворца и ей присвоено качество исторического сокровища Киото.</span></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span style="font-size:10pt; background-color: transparent"><br><br></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/CIMG7531%20%28420x315%29.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size:0in; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial" target=_blank><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452596220633/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/CIMG7531%20%28420x315%29.jpg?height=240&width=320" border="0" height="240px;" width="320px;" style="border: 0px; padding: 0px; width:274px; height:205px;"></span></a><span style="font-size:xx-small; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif"> <img src="http://www.city.kyoto.lg.jp/kensetu/cmsfiles/contents/0000020/20350/27ukyo.jpg" alt="&#19977;&#23542;&#23546;&#12398;&#12516;&#12510;&#12470;&#12463;&#12521;&#12398;&#20889;&#30495;"> </span><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/CIMG7524%20%28420x315%29.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: medium; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size:0in; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial" target=_blank><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1452596212061/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/CIMG7524%20%28420x315%29.jpg?height=240&width=320" border="0" height="240px;" width="320px;" style="border: 0px; padding: 0px; width:272px; height:205px;"></span></a></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><br><br></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span style="font-size:medium;"><span lang="ru"><span title="The temple has a great Shidare Sakura ( willowing cherry blossom called &quot; Gosha Gaeshi-no Sakura &quot; ) moved from Imperial Palace and it has been designated as a historical treasure of Kyoto.   "> </span><span title="There also is a great Shidare Sakura which is called &quot; Mata-eda Shidare Sakura = Split of Shidare Sakura of Maruyama Park &quot;.">Там также там есть большое дерево Shidare Сакура, которая называется &quot;Mata-eda Shidare Sakura&quot;. </span><span title="It is a sister of the famous Shidare Sakura of Maruyama Park in Higashiyama.">Эта сакура - сестра знаменитой Shidare Сакуры в парке Маруяма в Хигасияма. </span><span title="( The largest Shidere Sakura in Kyoto ).">(Крупнейшей Shidere Сакура в Киото).  Говорится</span></span><span style="background-color: transparent">, что красота этой сакуры заставляет людей возвращаться, чтобы увидеть ее снова.</span></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span style="background-color: transparent"><span style="font-size:medium;"> </span></span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><span style="font-size:medium;">Since the temple belongs to Nchiren sect, they also hold a ritual of &quot; Oeshiki &quot;. What is sppecial about the temple is that they sereve radish as a traditional remedy to prevent paralysis.</span></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><br><br></div><div style="font-family: Koulen, cursive; font-size:13px;"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sagano-arashiyama/sanbouji-temple-san-bao-si/CIMG7528%20%28315x420%29.jpg?attredirects=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: #551a8b; border-bottom-style: none; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: large; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size:0in; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-positi