        <span title="1 год 6 месяцев назад">00:39</span>&nbsp;<h2>Chionji Temple. Чионджи Хякуманбэн</h2>
</div>


    
    

    
        

               

                
    

    <div class="postContent">
        
                
                
                <div class="commentAuthor">
                    
                    <div class="sign">venzelesm@yandex.com</div>
                </div>
                
        

        <div class="postInner">
            <div class="paragraph">
                                
                <div style='min-height:40px'><h3><span style="font-size:large;"></span></h3><div align="center"><div align="center"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:large;">      &#12288;Чионджи.<br>Chionji Temple of Hyakumanben <br>&#30334;&#19975;&#36941;&#30693;&#24681;&#23546;<br>Hyakumanben area in Sakyo-ku &#30334;&#19975;&#32232;&#12539;&#24038;&#20140;&#21306;</span></span><br><br></div><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:large;"></span></span><div align="right"><span style="font-family: trebuchet ms,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:large;"><a href="https://goo.gl/maps/Az2zhRf9xrs" target=_blank>Location</a></span></span><br><br><br></div><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/kd229_12258-1396416084.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449624348809/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/kd229_12258-1396416084.jpg?height=266&width=400" border="0" height="266px;" width="400px;"></span></a><span style="font-size:xx-small;">  </span><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/9bb8df17-s.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449624338443/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/9bb8df17-s.jpg?height=300&width=400" style="width: 368px; height: 266px" border="0" height="300px;" width="400px;"></span></a><br><br><br></div><div><div style="text-align: left; display: block"><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'">ХякуманбэнТион-дзи расположен в районе Hyakumanben (около пересечения улицы Имадегава иулицы Хигащиоджи). </span><span title="It is a temple belongs to Jodo sect of Buddhism.">Это храм принадлежитсекте Дзедо буддизма. </span><span title="It is believed that the original form of this temple was founded by an old-time monk called Ennin in 9th century and later an important Buddhist priest called Honen opened a Buddhist school in this location.">Считается,что оригинальная форма этого храма был основана монах Ennin в 9-м веке, а позднееназвана важным буддистским священником <span> </span>Хонен,который открыл буддийскую школу в этом месте.<br></span><span title="It was the beginning of Chionji Temple of Hyakumanben.">Этобыло началом Chionji Храма Hyakumanben. </span><span title="A unique Buddhist ritual held in this temple is Rosary Handling.">Уникальныйбуддийский ритуал проводится в этом храме </span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'" lang="EN-US">Rosary</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'" lang="EN-US"> </span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'" lang="EN-US">Hendling</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'">. </span><span title="In this ritual, monks line up while chanting a sutra holding a huge rosary.">Вэтом ритуале, монахи выстраиваются в ряд и читают сутру, держа в руках огромныечетки. </span><span title="The ritual is open for regular visitors to join.">Ритуалв открытом доступе для постоянных посетителей. </span><span title="Nowadays the temple has been making a great use of its spacious ground to hold a big flea markets.">Внастоящее время на большой территории храма проводятся выставки-ярмарки товаровбывшего употребления, в основном книг.<br><b><br></b></span><div align="center"><b><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'">Дзедо буддизмв Японии</span></b><br></div><br><br><br><div style="text-align: left; display: block"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/300px-Aal_sized.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank><div style="text-align: center"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Buddha-flower-color.svg/100px-Buddha-flower-color.svg.png" alt="Buddha inside lotus" style="width: 102px; height: 97px" height="200px;" width="200px;"></div></a><br><br><br><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/300px-Aal_sized.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank><div style="text-align: center"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449626460065/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/maxresdefault.jpg?height=200&width=320" border="0" height="200px;" width="320px;">  <img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449626139609/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/%E7%84%A1%E9%A1%8C.png?height=200&width=190" border="0" height="200px;" width="190px;">  <img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449656966356/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/300px-Aal_sized.jpg?height=200&width=174" border="0" height="200px;" width="174px;"></div></a><br><br><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'">ДзедоСинсю </span><b><span style="font-size:13px; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'">J&#333;do <u>Shin</u>sh&#363;</span></b><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'"> <span> </span></span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'MS Mincho'" lang="EN-US">&#27972;&#22303;</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'" lang="EN-US"> </span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'MS Mincho'" lang="EN-US">&#30495;&#23447;</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'">&quot;Школа Истинно Чистой Земли&quot; , также известна как Shin буддизма, школаЧистой Земли буддизма. </span><span title="It was founded by the former Tendai Japanese monk Shinran.">Она былаоснована монахом, основателем Тэндай Shinran. </span><span title="Shin Buddhism is considered the most widely practiced branch of Buddhism in Japan, with 20% of the population of Japan identifying as members of the sect.">Шинбуддизм считается наиболее широко распространенным филиалом буддизма в Японии,20% населения Японии являются членами секты. </span><span title="Shinran in persuit of truih in his teachings of J&#333;do were completed by the enlightment of Honen.">Синранв преследовании истины в его учении Дзедо <span> </span>был завершен просвящением <span> </span>Хонен.<br></span><span title="H&#333;nen &#27861;&#28982; (1133 – 1212) is the religious reformer and founder of the first independent branch of J&#333;do-sh&#363; &#27972;&#22303;&#23447;, &quot;The Pure Land School&quot;.">Хонен</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'MS Mincho'" lang="EN-US">&#27861;</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'" lang="EN-US"> </span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'MS Mincho'" lang="EN-US">&#28982;</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'"> (1133- 1212) является религиозный реформатором и основателем первой независимойветви Дзедо-шу </span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'MS Mincho'" lang="EN-US">&#27972;&#22303;</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'" lang="EN-US"> </span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'MS Mincho'" lang="EN-US">&#23447;</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'">, &quot;Чистая Земля&quot; Школа. </span><span title="He is also considered the Seventh J&#333;do Shinsh&#363; Patriarch.">Он такжесчитается Седьмой Дзедо Синсю Патриарх. </span><span title="Later on, Honen undertook the teaching of rebirth in the pure land of Amit&#257;bha through nianfo or &quot;recitation of the Buddha's name&quot;. ">Позже,Хонен предпринял учение перерождения в чистой земле Амитабхи через nianfo или&quot;чтение имени Будды&quot;.</span><br><br></div></div></div><div align="center"><span style="font-size:large; color: #0000ff"><b>Web-link :</b></span>  <span style="font-size:large;"><b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pure_Land_Buddhism" rel="nofollow" target=_blank>Pure Land Buddhism</a></b> &#27972;&#22303;&#30495;&#23447; <a href="http://www.jodo.org/" rel="nofollow" target=_blank>http://www.jodo.org/</a></span></div><div align="center"><span style="font-size:medium;"><div><div class="sites-embed-align-left-wrapping-off"><div class="sites-embed-border-on sites-embed" style="width:640px;"><h4>  <a href="http://youtu.be/S_n1V-Be5Do" target="_blank">youtu.be/S_n1V-Be5Do</a></h4></div></div></div></span></div><div align="center"><span style="font-size:large;">Ежемесячная ярмарка 15го числа.</span><br><br></div><div><div align="center"><span style="font-size:medium;"><div style="text-align: left; display: block"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/o0640048012782021754.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank><div style="text-align: center"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449626825642/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/20140915_951099.jpg?height=300&width=400" style="width: 347px; height: 253px" border="0" height="300px;" width="400px;">  <img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449624353587/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/o0640048012782021754.jpg?height=299&width=400" style="width: 341px; height: 253px" border="0" height="299px;" width="400px;"></div></a></div></span></div><span style="font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:xx-small;"> </span></span><span style="font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'"> </span><span title="This temple has raised its popularity with its monthly handicraft market called ( Tezukuri-ichi = Handmade flea market ) these days.">Этотхрам повысил популярность своим ежемесячным ремесленническим рынком подназванием Tezukuri-</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'" lang="EN-US">ichi</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'"> = <span> </span>блошиныйрынок рукоделия. </span><span title="The market is held every 15th of the month.">Рынок проводится15 числа каждого месяца.</span></span></span><div align="center"><span style="font-size:medium;"><div><div class="sites-embed-align-left-wrapping-off"><div class="sites-embed-border-on sites-embed" style="width:640px;"><h4><a href="http://youtu.be/DiPvL80AV9U" target="_blank">youtu.be/DiPvL80AV9U</a></h4></div></div></div></span></div></div><div align="center"><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'">Если вы посетите эту ярмарку, найдите магазинчик</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'"><span> </span>Ами! У неезамечательные изделия ручной работы.</span><br></div><br><br><div><span style="font-size:medium;"><span style="background-color: #274e13"><span style="color: #ffffff"><span style="background-color: #ff9900"><span style="background-color: #e06666"><span style="font-size:x-large;"><span style="color: #000000"><span style="background-color: #783f04"><span style="color: #fff2cc"><span style="font-family: georgia,serif"><span style="background-color: #783f04"><div><span style="font-family: georgia,serif"><div style="text-align: left; display: block"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-promotion-business/Handmade%20Ami%20%20%281%29.JPG?attredirects=0" target=_blank><span style="font-size:xx-small;"></span></a><div style="text-align: center"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-promotion-business/Handmade%20Ami%20%20%281%29.JPG?attredirects=0" target=_blank><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1447377386014/tgm-promotion-business/Handmade%20Ami%20%20%282%29.JPG?height=240&width=320" border="0" height="240px;" width="320px;">     <img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1447377386014/tgm-promotion-business/Handmade%20Ami%20%20%281%29.JPG?height=240&width=320" border="0" height="240px;" width="320px;"> <br></a><b><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-promotion-business/handmade-artist-ami-handomeido-zuo-jia-ya-wei" target=_blank>Handmade Artist Ami    &#12495;&#12531;&#12489;&#12513;&#12452;&#12489;&#20316;&#23478; &#20124;&#26410;</a></b><br></div></div></span></div></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><br><div><div style="text-align: center"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449626830679/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/20101101221439e23.jpg?height=400&width=299" border="0" height="400px;" width="299px;">   <img src="http://www.tedukuri-ichi.com/hyakumanben/image/hyakumanben-map.jpg" style="margin-top: 3px" height="400px;" width="400px;"></div><b><span title="Don't get Chionji mixed up with Chion-in">Непутайте Chionji и </span></b><b><span lang="EN-US">Chionin</span>.</b><br><p class="MsoNormal" align="center"><br><span title="Many people mistake this Chionji for Chionin which is located next to Shoren-in.">Многие люди ошибочно путают Chionji и Chionin, который находится рядом с Сёрэн-ин. </span><span title="These two names are similar spelling and sound.">Эти два названия похожипо орфографии и зпроизношению. </span></p><div align="center"><span title="The location of Chionji temple is in Hyakumanben, in front of Kyoto university."><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'">Расположение храма Chionji в Hyakumanben, напротивКиотского университета.</span></span><br><br><span title="The location of Chionji temple is in Hyakumanben, in front of Kyoto university."><span title="A second-hand book market is also held every autumn ( around Oct 30th - Nov 5th )."><span> </span><span> </span>Рынок подержанных книг <span> </span>также проводится каждую осень (~ 30 окт - 5 ноября).</span></span><br></div><br><div style="text-align: left; display: block"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/huruhonmaturi01.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank><span style="font-size:medium;"><div style="text-align: center"><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449641023078/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/20140818175700350_0001.jpg?height=320&width=226" border="0" height="320px;" width="226px;">    <img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449624343386/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si/huruhonmaturi01.jpg" border="0"> </div></span></a></div></div></div><div><span style="font-size:medium;"><br></span><div align="center"><span style="font-size:medium;"><b><span style="color: #0000ff">Web-link</span> ( Chionji Home ) : </b></span><a href="http://hyakusan.jp/" rel="nofollow" target=_blank><span style="font-size:medium;"><b>http://hyakusan.jp/</b></span></a></div></div><div align="center"><span style="font-size:medium;"><b><span style="color: #0000ff">Web-link</span> ( Flea market ) : </b></span><a href="http://www.tedukuri-ichi.com/" rel="nofollow" target=_blank><span style="font-size:medium;"><b>http://www.tedukuri-ichi.com/</b></span></a></div><div align="center"><span style="font-size:medium;"><br><b>Address :</b> 103 Tanaka Monzen-cho, Sakyo-ku, Kyoto</span> </div>  <br><div align="center">info in English <br><b><span style="color: #993366"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/sakyo-ku/chionji-temple-of-hyakumanben-bai-wan-bian-zhi-en-si" target=_blank>TGM Kyoto</a></span></b></div></div>
