b><span style="background-color: #444444; font-size:large; color: #ffffff"> </span></b><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'"><b>УлицаГоджё - Годжё-зака (Дорога к Храму Kiyomizu)</b></span></div><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%; font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'"><b><br><br></b></span></div></div><div align="center"><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/higashiyama-ku-dong-shan-qu/wakamiya-hachimangu-sha-ruo-gong-ba-fan-gong-she/69a3feb3a415fc63bd91330904ba4d76.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449541107546/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/higashiyama-ku-dong-shan-qu/wakamiya-hachimangu-sha-ruo-gong-ba-fan-gong-she/69a3feb3a415fc63bd91330904ba4d76.jpg?height=266&width=400" border="0" height="266px;" width="400px;"></a><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/higashiyama-ku-dong-shan-qu/wakamiya-hachimangu-sha-ruo-gong-ba-fan-gong-she/ef1eee4233f0bd5974a0433e7b9854c7.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank> <img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449541112142/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/higashiyama-ku-dong-shan-qu/wakamiya-hachimangu-sha-ruo-gong-ba-fan-gong-she/ef1eee4233f0bd5974a0433e7b9854c7.jpg?height=266&width=400" border="0" height="266px;" width="400px;"></a></div> </div></span></div><span style="font-size:small;"><div><div style="text-align: left; display: block"><span style="font-size:xx-small;"> </span></div><div style="text-align: left; display: block" align="center"><span style="font-family: georgia,palatino"><span style="font-size:medium;"><br></span></span><div align="center"><span style="font-family: georgia,palatino"><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%;">Этачасть улицы Gojo подключен к улице под названием Годжё-зака (холмистый Годжё). </span><span title="Gojozaka is a sloping path leading you to Kiyomizu Temple up on the hill.">Gojozaka–дорога, ведущая вверх на холм к храму Киёмидзу, расположенном на холме. </span><span title="Just on the east side of the bypass on the picture above on the left is Otani Honbyo cemetary.">Навосточной стороне объездной дороги на картинке выше слева находится кладбище </span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%;" lang="EN-US">Otani</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%;"> Honbyo. </span><span title="&quot;Gojo-zaka"> </span></span><br><span style="font-family: georgia,palatino"><span title="&quot;Gojo-zaka">Гожо-зака является улицей, которая идет на восток и северо-запад <span> </span>Отани Honbyo.<br></span></span><a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/higashiyama-ku-dong-shan-qu/wakamiya-hachimangu-sha-ruo-gong-ba-fan-gong-she/CIMG2785.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449542558776/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/higashiyama-ku-dong-shan-qu/wakamiya-hachimangu-sha-ruo-gong-ba-fan-gong-she/CIMG2785.jpg?height=299&width=400" border="0" height="299px;" width="400px;"></a> <a href="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/higashiyama-ku-dong-shan-qu/wakamiya-hachimangu-sha-ruo-gong-ba-fan-gong-she/118691124577816122723.jpg?attredirects=0" target=_blank><img src="https://sites.google.com/a/transwordtgm.com/https-sites-google-com-a-transwordtgm-com-sites/_/rsrc/1449542554019/tgm-international/tgm-kyoto-guide/higashiyama-ku-dong-shan-qu/wakamiya-hachimangu-sha-ruo-gong-ba-fan-gong-she/118691124577816122723.jpg?height=299&width=400" border="0" height="299px;" width="400px;"></a></div></div><div><div style="text-align: left; display: block"><span style="font-size:xx-small;"> </span></div><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family: georgia,palatino"><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%;"></span></span></span></span><br><div align="center"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family: georgia,palatino"><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%;"></span><span title="You will come to this point where the road splits in 2 ways.">Вы придетек этой развилке. </span><span title="The path on the left is Chawan-zaka and the path on the right is Gojo-zaka.">Путьналево Chawan-</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%;" lang="EN-US">zaka</span><span style="font-size:11pt; line-height:100%;"> и путь по правой дороге - Годжё-зака. </span><span title="Gojo-zaka district is also Kyoto's center for ceramics and home to many of the area's master potter studios, with the diverse festival stalls lining the street all the way to Kiyomizu Temple.">РайонГоджё-зака -также центр керамики Киото и дома-мастерские-студии <span> </span>гончарного дела. <span> </span>Вдоль улицы множество магазинов, продающихкерамические изделия. Храм Киёмидзу и округа является одним из самых оживленныхрайонов с туристами в Киото. </span></span><span title="If you are visiting during holiday season, it is recommended that you pick one of weekdays."><span style="font-family: georgia,palatino">Есливы приехали в курортный сезон, рекомендуется, чтобы вы выбрали один из буднихдней.</span></span></span></span><br></div><div align="center"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span title="If you are visiting during holiday season, it is recommended that you pick one of weekdays."></span></span></span><br><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span title="If you are visiting during holiday season, it is re